<div class="mt-6 pt-8 px-4 border-t border-warm-grey text-xs text-mid-grey leading-relaxed">
	<div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
		<p><strong class="text-dark-grey">AEMO ISP</strong> — The Integrated System Plan, published by the Australian Energy Market Operator, is a whole-of-system roadmap for the efficient development of the NEM over the next 20+ years.</p>
		<p><strong class="text-dark-grey">Scenarios</strong> — Each ISP models multiple plausible futures varying assumptions about economic growth, policy ambition, technology costs and consumer behaviour (e.g. Step Change, Progressive Change).</p>
		<p><strong class="text-dark-grey">CDP</strong> — Candidate Development Pathway. A sequence of infrastructure investments (generation, storage and transmission) evaluated within each scenario.</p>
		<p><strong class="text-dark-grey">ODP</strong> — Optimal Development Pathway. The recommended CDP that best balances cost, reliability and risk across scenarios.</p>
		<p class="mt-2">For more info, see the <a href="https://aemo.com.au/energy-systems/electricity/national-electricity-market-nem/nem-forecasting-and-planning/integrated-system-plan-isp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-mid-grey underline">AEMO Integrated System Plan for the National Electricity Market</a>.</p>
	</div>
</div>
